com.arkoisystems.arkoicompiler.stage.syntaxAnalyzer.ast.types

Class BlockSyntaxAST

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.arkoisystems.arkoicompiler.stage.syntaxAnalyzer.ast.AbstractSyntaxAST
      • com.arkoisystems.arkoicompiler.stage.syntaxAnalyzer.ast.types.BlockSyntaxAST

  • public class BlockSyntaxAST
extends AbstractSyntaxAST
    Used if you want to create a new BlockSyntaxAST. But it is recommend to use the BLOCK_PARSER to parse a new BlockSyntaxAST because with it you can check if the current AbstractToken is capable to parse this AST.

      • blockType

        @Expose
private BlockType blockType
        Defines the type of the BlockSyntaxAST. It can be an inlined block or just a block. An example for this is:

        Inlined-Block:

             fun greeting() = "Hello World";

        or

        Block:

              fun main(args: string[]) {
          return 0;
      }

    • Method Detail

      • parseAST

        public BlockSyntaxAST parseAST(AbstractSyntaxAST parentAST,
                               SyntaxAnalyzer syntaxAnalyzer)
        Parses a new BlockSyntaxAST with the given parameters, where the SyntaxAnalyzer is used to check the syntax and the parent AbstractSyntaxAST is used to see if this AST can be created inside the parent. It will parse every AbstractSyntaxAST which is included in the BLOCK_PARSERS array. Also the method will set if the block is inlined or not.

        Inlined-Block:

             fun greeting() = "Hello World";

        or

        Block:

              fun main(args: string[]) {
          return 0;
      }
        Specified by:
        parseAST in class AbstractSyntaxAST
        Parameters:
        parentAST - the parent AbstractSyntaxAST which should get used to check if the AbstractSyntaxAST can be created inside it.
        syntaxAnalyzer - the SyntaxAnalyzer which is used for checking the syntax with methods like SyntaxAnalyzer.matchesCurrentToken(TokenType) )} or SyntaxAnalyzer.matchesNextToken(AbstractNumberToken.NumberType).
        Returns:
        null if an error occurred or the BlockSyntaxAST if everything worked correctly.
